    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** leading our projections at an elite 82.13. His matchup against Roki Sasaki is particularly favorable; the combination of a +19% SP skill adjustment and a +14% platoon edge, bolstered by a wind-out environment, makes him our must-start asset. **Junior Caminero** also projects as a high-upside play at 73.53, capitalizing on a strong SP skill bonus against Bailey Ober. While **Trea Turner** (68.86) and **Kyle Schwarber** (65.76) face the moderate arm of Bryce Elder, their locked-in status in the top two spots of the order ensures they remain core contributors for Roto categories today.\n\nPlatoon advantages and environmental factors remain our primary tools for volatility management. **Colt Keith** (62.83) benefits from a solid 7% platoon boost against Brady Singer, whereas **Yordan Alvarez** (62.54) has been downgraded slightly due to a significant -9% L/L platoon penalty against Ryan Weathers, though his raw talent keeps him in the optimal lineup. The most difficult decision involved **Josh Smith** (44.87) on the bench. He narrowly missed the cut; while his 86% SB success rate against a slow pitcher delivery offered intriguing speed potential, the -15% penalty against the left-handed Jeffrey Springs ultimately pushed the optimizer toward **Luke Raley** (45.69), who holds a higher base projection despite his own platoon constraints.\n\nManagers should note that all projected scores currently rely on \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions. Any late shifts in batting order\u2014specifically for **Dillon Dingler** and **Gary Sanchez**\u2014could drastically alter their daily efficiency. Furthermore, while **Hyeseong Kim** (57.68) remains a strategic hold for his 63% SB potential, his low order position and the inherent risk of the 4.36 xERA match against Colin Rea require close monitoring. We continue to prioritize speed-heavy profiles like those of **Victor Scott II**\u2014who remains on the bench today due to a tough matchup against Bryan Woo\u2014to ensure we maintain our edge in the scarcest category.",
